<html>
<head>
<title>External Stylesheets</title>
<link rel="stylesheet" href="styles/forms.less">
<style>
body {
  font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, sans-serif;
  background: #f5f5f5;
  margin: 0;
  padding: 2rem;
}

.container {
  max-width: 600px;
  margin: 0 auto;
  background: white;
  border-radius: 8px;
  padding: 2rem;
  box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
}

h1 {
  color: #2c3e50;
  margin-top: 0;
}

.example {
  margin: 2rem 0;
}
</style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="container">
<h1>External Stylesheets</h1>

<p>You can link to external <code>.css</code> or <code>.less</code> files using standard HTML <code>&lt;link&gt;</code> tags.</p>

<div class="example">
<h2>Form Example</h2>
<form>
<div class="form-group">
<label for="email">Email Address</label>
<input type="email" id="email" placeholder="your@email.com" required>
</div>

<div class="form-group">
<label for="password">Password</label>
<input type="password" id="password" placeholder="Enter password" required>
</div>

<div class="form-actions">
<button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary">Submit</button>
<button type="reset" class="btn btn-secondary">Clear</button>
</div>
</form>
</div>

<p>The form styling comes from the external <code>styles/forms.less</code> file which is compiled and served as CSS.</p>
</div>
</body>
</html>
